sequenceDiagram
  actor Admin
  actor Operator
  participant Web as React Web Client
  participant API as KnowledgeController
  participant Guard as AdminGuard
  participant CLI as knowledge:sync CLI
  participant Knowledge as KnowledgeService
  participant Pack as KnowledgePackService
  participant DB as SQLite
  participant AIModel as AiModelService
  participant Files as OpenAI Files API
  participant Vectors as OpenAI Vector Stores

  rect rgb(245,245,245)
  Note over Admin,Vectors: Manual admin upload
  Admin->>Web: Select PDF/MD/TXT/DOCX/TeX file
  Web->>API: POST /admin/knowledge/files multipart
  API->>Guard: Validate admin session
  Guard-->>API: Admin user
  API->>Knowledge: uploadKnowledgeFile(file)
  Knowledge->>Knowledge: Validate non-empty file, extension, 25 MB controller limit
  Knowledge->>DB: Read active vector store ids
  alt No vector store exists
    Knowledge->>AIModel: Create vector store
    AIModel->>Vectors: OpenAI vector store request
    Vectors-->>AIModel: vector_store_id
    AIModel-->>Knowledge: vector store response
  end
  Knowledge->>AIModel: Upload file
  AIModel->>Files: OpenAI file upload
  Files-->>AIModel: openai_file_id
  AIModel-->>Knowledge: file response
  Knowledge->>AIModel: Attach file to vector store
  AIModel->>Vectors: OpenAI vector attachment
  Vectors-->>AIModel: status
  AIModel-->>Knowledge: attachment response
  Knowledge->>DB: Insert knowledge_files metadata
  Knowledge->>DB: Upsert project_ai_resources when env ids are absent
  Knowledge-->>API: KnowledgeFileDto
  API-->>Web: Uploaded file metadata
  Web->>API: GET /admin/knowledge/status
  API->>Knowledge: getStatus()
  Knowledge->>AIModel: Refresh vector file statuses
  AIModel->>Vectors: List vector store files
  Vectors-->>AIModel: File statuses
  AIModel-->>Knowledge: Status response
  Knowledge->>DB: Update and read metadata
  API-->>Web: vectorStoreIds and files
  end

  rect rgb(245,245,245)
  Note over Operator,Vectors: Local knowledge-pack import and optional RAG sync
  Operator->>CLI: npm run knowledge:sync -- --pack <zip> --import-db [--sync-rag] [--dry-run]
  CLI->>Pack: Resolve zip or extracted root
  opt Import structured DB files
    Pack->>DB: Read knowledge_source_files hashes
    alt Structured source unchanged
      Pack->>DB: Mark source file skipped
    else New or changed structured source
      Pack->>DB: Upsert curriculum, task bank, misconceptions, lesson plans
      Pack->>DB: Record source path, hash, and import ledger
    end
  end
  opt Sync student-facing Markdown to RAG
    Pack->>Knowledge: syncRagSourceFile(relativePath, sha256)
    alt dry-run
      Knowledge-->>Pack: Planned upload/replace without OpenAI calls
    else Same hash already active
      Knowledge->>DB: Record skipped source state
    else New or changed Markdown
      Knowledge->>AIModel: Upload file
      AIModel->>Files: OpenAI file upload
      Files-->>AIModel: openai_file_id
      Knowledge->>AIModel: Attach new file to vector store
      AIModel->>Vectors: OpenAI vector attachment
      Vectors-->>AIModel: status
      Knowledge->>DB: Insert active knowledge_files row and project_ai_resources id
      opt Older synced file exists
        Knowledge->>AIModel: Remove old file from vector store
        AIModel->>Vectors: DELETE /vector_stores/{vector_store_id}/files/{file_id}
        Vectors-->>AIModel: deletion status
        Knowledge->>DB: Mark old knowledge_files row superseded
      end
    end
  end
  Pack->>DB: Insert knowledge_pack_imports summary
  end
